{center}
{subhead}*25.4.2000 fxPAINT EK #2 completed*{def}
{left}
{p} {p}
The second update for fxPAINT has been completed and offers many new
features. Thanks to many optimizations, a higher speed could be achieved. The most
important changes since EK #1:
{p} {p}
    fxVIDEO-System: Tutorial-videos are now possible directly from within
fxPAINT!{p}
    new drawing utility: bevelcircle{p}
    6 new effects (Edge-Detect, Sharpen, Texture, "Deep inside",
DisplaceMap and a new buttonborder-effect){p}
    real antialiasing for text{p}
    improved tableau-support{p}
    vastly improved fxALBUM (especially improved HTML-Album-creation){p}
    wap.plugin: fxPAINT is the first and only program on the AMIGA, that
can read and write WBMP-images!{p}
    AXIS-color calibration system for optimized screen-display{p}
    Mousewheel-support for mice that support the NewMouse-standard (e.g.
VMC 4D+ mouse){p}
    improved loader- and saver-speed thanks to the PPC
{p} {p}
Furthermore many improvements in detail have been made, that were
inspired by users.
{p} {p}
{center}
{subhead}*23.3.2000 VHI Studio 5.0 available*{def}
{left}
{p} {p}
Today, Innovative released VHI Studio 5, the successor of the well-known
VLRec NG.
{p} {p}
This software allows recording, editing and grabbing via a
digitizer-board (various are supported via VHI, e.g. VLab, FrameMachine, Masoboshi MVD 819, GVP
IV24) or digital camera. Further extras like manipulation of images, animated
effects, webcam-and timelapse-creation-capabilities are available as well. With VHI
Studio it is now even possible to access all image-data as if they were saved on a
harddisk.
{p} {p}
New features compared to VLRec NG 4.0 are:{p}
  - DigiCam-support added{p}
        Support for serial-numbers and therfore the ability to create commercial VHI-drivers for DigiCams{p}
        Read-in the content of the DigiCam's memory into the Snapshot-Center{p}
        Information on the snapped picture are displayed in the Snapshot-Center{p}
        Information about the status of the camera can be shown{p}
        Pictures can be taken by pressing a button{p}
{p} {p}
  - direct process-possibilites within the Snapshot Center{p}
        Mirror-functions{p}
        Rotation-functions{p}
        Optimizations{p}
{p} {p}
  - New driver CamEx.vhi{p}
        three virtual inputs with different animations (these are transfered as JPEG to VHI Studio and are decoded in realtime){p}
        Simulation of a DigiCam (only limitation: The simulation does not store information on which pictures should be deleted from the cams memory)
{p} {p}
  - VHI Studio VD (Virtual Disk){p}
        all imagedata in memory is available as files{p}
        MPEG-Encoding does no more require ANY temporary files{p}
          - Save space on your HD{p}
          - faster encoding, as the imagedata is no more loaded from HD but from the much faster memory and also doesn't have to be saved previously{p}
        Access to DigiCams as if they were harddisks
{p} {p}
  - Multichannel-preview (watch up to nine inputs at once){p}
  - new driver for the GVP IV24{p}
  - Driver for Olympus-DigiCams is available optionally{p}
  - Driver for Kodak-DigiCams is available optionally {p}
  - Direct support of Picasso 96 (not until now via the
cybergraphics.library-Emulation of P96){p}
  - Loading of new pictures in the Snapshot Center is now possible{p}
  - IFF-ILBM-Files can now be loaded and saved
{p} {p}
At the same time, Innovative released three new VHI-DigiCam-drivers, that
allow users to run up-to-date devices on their AMIGA. The following cameras are supported by
the current drivers olympus.vhi, kodak_dc21x.vhi and kodak_dc2_48.vhi:
{p} {p}
  - Olympus{p}
        Camedia C-420L{p}
        Camedia C-820L{p}
        Camedia C-830L{p}
        Camedia C-840L{p}
        Camedia C-900Z{p}
        Camedia C-920Z{p}
        Camedia C-1000L{p}
        Camedia C-1200Z{p}
        Camedia C-1400L/XL{p}
        Camedia C-2000Z{p}
        Camedia C-21{p}
        Camedia C-2500{p}
{p} {p}
  - Nikon{p}
        Coolpix 700
{p} {p}
  - Kodak{p}
        DC 200{p}
        DC 200+{p}
        DC 210{p}
        DC 210+{p}
        DC 215{p}
        DC 240{p}
        DC 240i{p}
        DC 280
{p} {p}
VHI Studio is delivered on CD with all VHI-drivers and CPU-optimized
versions of the program as well as some goodies and developer-information.
Drivers for DigiCams are delivered seperatly.
{p} {p}
Pricing:{p}
  - VHI Studio: 69 DM/35 EURO/35 US${p}
  - VHI-DigiCam-driver: 20 DM/10 EURO/10 US${p}
{p} {p}
